	<h2>Feedback</h2>
	<p>If you are interested in the RECOIL project, please subscribe its
	<a href="https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/recoil-users">mailing list</a>.
	This list is for users and developers.
	Once you subscribe, you can post comments, ideas and questions about RECOIL.</p>
	<p>You may submit bugs <a href="http://sourceforge.net/p/recoil/bugs/">here</a>.</p>

	<h2>For software developers</h2>
	<p>Download the latest source release: <download prefix="recoil-" suffix=".tar.gz" />
	or <a href="https://sourceforge.net/p/recoil/code/ci/master/tree/">browse Git repository</a>.</p>
	<p>RECOIL is based on a development library, which you can easily embed in your program.
	It's not only a fully portable C library - it's better than that.
	Since RECOIL is written in <a href="http://cito.sourceforge.net/">Ć</a>,
	it is also available as pure Java, C#, JavaScript, ActionScript, Perl and <a href="http://dlang.org/">D</a>.</p>
	<p>There are also <a href="https://github.com/gasman/pyrecoil">Python bindings</a>.</p>
